---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import { withBase } from '../config';
---

<Base
  title="Primer: Ontology Matching"
  description="A gentle, interactive introduction to ontology matching and the two DISO-OAEI tasks — build a small alignment, then rank candidates with NIL abstention."
>
  <div class="page-head">
    <div class="container">
      <nav class="crumbs" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
        <a href={withBase('/')}>Home</a><span class="sep" aria-hidden="true">/</span><span aria-current="page">Primer</span>
      </nav>
      <h1>A Primer on Ontology Matching</h1>
      <p class="lead">
        New to the field? This page explains what the track asks systems to do, then lets you
        try both tasks by hand on toy examples.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <section class="section" style="border-top:none;" aria-labelledby="what-h">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="prose">
        <h2 id="what-h" style="border-top:none; padding-top:0; margin-top:0;">What is an ontology?</h2>
        <p>
          An <strong>ontology</strong> is a formal, machine-readable vocabulary for a domain: its
          <em>classes</em> (kinds of things, e.g. <code>TemperatureSensor</code>), its
          <em>properties</em> (relations and attributes, e.g. <code>isLocatedIn</code>), and the
          logical axioms connecting them. Two organisations modelling the same world almost never
          produce the same ontology — names, granularity, and structure all differ.
        </p>
        <h2>What is ontology matching?</h2>
        <p>
          <strong>Ontology matching</strong> (or <em>alignment</em>) is the task of automatically
          finding which entities in one ontology correspond to which entities in another. A single
          finding is a <strong>correspondence</strong>:
        </p>
        <p>
          <code>⟨ entity₁, entity₂, relation, confidence ⟩</code> — for example
          <code>⟨ thinkhome:CoolCommand, brick:Cooling_Command, =, 1.0 ⟩</code>.
        </p>
        <p>
          A set of correspondences between two ontologies is an <strong>alignment</strong>. Matching
          systems are evaluated by comparing their alignment against a <strong>reference
          alignment</strong> curated by experts. DISO-OAEI's references are <em>partial but locally
          complete</em> "silver standards": for every entity they mention, they list all of that
          entity's correct correspondences — but they are silent about unmentioned entities. The
          scoring accounts for this (that's the "partiality-corrected" in our metrics: predictions
          the reference cannot adjudicate don't count against you).
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="demo" id="matching-demo">
        <h3>Try it — Task 1 in miniature</h3>
        <p class="hint">
          Two toy ontologies. Select one entity on each side to propose a correspondence, then watch
          precision, recall and F1 respond. The hidden reference covers only the
          <em>sensor / heating / window</em> entities — <code>Room ↔ Space</code> is a perfectly
          good mapping the silver simply doesn't mention, so proposing it neither helps nor hurts.
          That is partiality correction at work.
        </p>
        <noscript><p class="hint"><strong>The interactive demo needs JavaScript.</strong> A worked example: proposing TemperatureSensor↔Temperature_Sensor and Heater↔Lighting_System gives Â = 2 judgeable proposals, 1 correct: P = 1/2 = 0.50, R = 1/3 ≈ 0.33, F1 = 0.40.</p></noscript>
        <div class="demo-cols">
          <div class="entity-list" id="md-left">
            <span class="col-label">HomeOnt (source)</span>
          </div>
          <div class="entity-list" id="md-right">
            <span class="col-label">BuildOnt (target)</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <ul class="match-list" id="md-matches" aria-label="Your proposed correspondences"></ul>
        <div class="score-chips" id="md-score" aria-live="polite"></div>
      </div>

      <div class="prose">
        <h2>When there is no right answer: ranking with NIL</h2>
        <p>
          Task 2 flips the problem around. Instead of generating an alignment, a system receives,
          for each <em>query</em> (a source entity), a fixed pool of 50 candidate targets and must
          order the pool <strong>best-first</strong>. One special candidate — <strong>NIL</strong> —
          means <em>"no equivalent exists."</em> Ranking NIL first is how a system abstains.
          Scoring simply asks: <em>where in your ranking did the right answer land?</em>
          Hits&#64;k is the fraction of queries whose right answer is in the top k;
          MRR averages 1/rank.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="demo" id="ranking-demo">
        <h3>Try it — Task 2 in miniature</h3>
        <p class="hint">
          Reorder the candidate pool with the arrow buttons. The gold answer is tagged so you can
          see exactly how the metrics respond to its position. Toggle the query type to see how
          abstention (NIL-first) is scored when no equivalent exists.
        </p>
        <noscript><p class="hint"><strong>The interactive demo needs JavaScript.</strong> A worked example: if the gold target sits at rank 2 of 6, it contributes Hits@1 = 0, Hits@3 = Hits@5 = 1, and reciprocal rank 1/2 = 0.5.</p></noscript>
        <p style="font-size:0.92rem;">
          Query: <code>uco:Identity</code> <span class="badge">CLS</span>
          <label style="margin-left:1rem; font-size:0.88rem;">
            <input type="checkbox" id="rd-nil-mode" />
            make this a NIL query (no equivalent exists)
          </label>
        </p>
        <ol class="rank-list" id="rd-list" aria-label="Your ranking, best first"></ol>
        <div class="score-chips" id="rd-score" aria-live="polite"></div>
      </div>

      <div class="prose">
        <h2>Where to go next</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><a href={withBase('/quickstart/')}>Quickstart</a> — download the data and validate a submission in minutes.</li>
          <li><a href={withBase('/tasks/global/')}>Task 1 — Global alignment</a> and its <a href={withBase('/tasks/global/submission-format/')}>submission format</a>.</li>
          <li><a href={withBase('/tasks/ranking/')}>Task 2 — Equivalence ranking</a> and its <a href={withBase('/tasks/ranking/submission-format/')}>submission format</a>.</li>
          <li><a href={withBase('/evaluation/')}>Evaluation metrics</a> — the formal definitions.</li>
          <li><a href="https://oaei.ontologymatching.org/">The OAEI</a> — the wider evaluation initiative this track belongs to.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>

<script>
  // ---------- Demo 1: partial-reference alignment scoring ----------
  {
    const LEFT = ['Room', 'TemperatureSensor', 'Heater', 'WindowContact', 'EnergyMeter'];
    const RIGHT = ['Space', 'Temperature_Sensor', 'HVAC_Heating_System', 'Window_Status_Sensor', 'Lighting_System'];
    const REF = new Set([
      'TemperatureSensor|Temperature_Sensor',
      'Heater|HVAC_Heating_System',
      'WindowContact|Window_Status_Sensor',
    ]);
    const COVERED_L = new Set(['TemperatureSensor', 'Heater', 'WindowContact']);
    const COVERED_R = new Set(['Temperature_Sensor', 'HVAC_Heating_System', 'Window_Status_Sensor']);

    const leftBox = document.getElementById('md-left');
    const rightBox = document.getElementById('md-right');
    const matchUl = document.getElementById('md-matches');
    const scoreBox = document.getElementById('md-score');
    if (leftBox && rightBox && matchUl && scoreBox) {
      let selL: string | null = null;
      let selR: string | null = null;
      const proposals: Array<[string, string]> = [];

      const mkBtn = (name: string, side: 'l' | 'r') => {
        const b = document.createElement('button');
        b.type = 'button';
        b.className = 'entity';
        b.textContent = name;
        b.setAttribute('aria-pressed', 'false');
        b.addEventListener('click', () => {
          if (side === 'l') selL = selL === name ? null : name;
          else selR = selR === name ? null : name;
          if (selL && selR) {
            if (!proposals.some(([a, c]) => a === selL && c === selR)) proposals.push([selL, selR]);
            selL = null;
            selR = null;
          }
          renderAll();
        });
        return b;
      };
      LEFT.forEach((n) => leftBox.append(mkBtn(n, 'l')));
      RIGHT.forEach((n) => rightBox.append(mkBtn(n, 'r')));

      const renderAll = () => {
        leftBox.querySelectorAll('.entity').forEach((b) => {
          b.setAttribute('aria-pressed', String(b.textContent === selL));
          b.classList.toggle('matched', proposals.some(([a]) => a === b.textContent));
        });
        rightBox.querySelectorAll('.entity').forEach((b) => {
          b.setAttribute('aria-pressed', String(b.textContent === selR));
          b.classList.toggle('matched', proposals.some(([, c]) => c === b.textContent));
        });

        matchUl.innerHTML = '';
        proposals.forEach(([a, c], i) => {
          const li = document.createElement('li');
          const judgeable = COVERED_L.has(a) || COVERED_R.has(c);
          const inRef = REF.has(`${a}|${c}`);
          const verdict = !judgeable ? '○ not judgeable (uncovered)' : inRef ? '✓ agrees with reference' : '✗ contradicts reference';
          const color = !judgeable ? 'var(--ink-3)' : inRef ? 'var(--ok)' : 'var(--warn-ink)';
          li.innerHTML = `<code>${a}</code> <span class="arrow" aria-hidden="true">↔</span> <code>${c}</code> <span class="verdict" style="color:${color}">${verdict}</span>`;
          const rm = document.createElement('button');
          rm.type = 'button';
          rm.textContent = 'remove';
          rm.setAttribute('aria-label', `Remove proposal ${a} to ${c}`);
          rm.addEventListener('click', () => {
            proposals.splice(i, 1);
            renderAll();
            // keep keyboard users in the list instead of dropping focus to <body>
            const btns = matchUl.querySelectorAll<HTMLElement>('button');
            const next = btns[Math.min(i, btns.length - 1)];
            (next ?? leftBox.querySelector<HTMLElement>('.entity'))?.focus();
          });
          li.append(rm);
          matchUl.append(li);
        });

        const judgeable = proposals.filter(([a, c]) => COVERED_L.has(a) || COVERED_R.has(c));
        const correct = proposals.filter(([a, c]) => REF.has(`${a}|${c}`)).length;
        const P = judgeable.length ? correct / judgeable.length : null;
        const R = correct / REF.size;
        const F1 = P !== null && P + R > 0 ? (2 * P * R) / (P + R) : null;
        const fmt = (x: number | null) => (x === null ? '—' : x.toFixed(2));
        scoreBox.innerHTML = `
          <span class="chip">proposals <strong>${proposals.length}</strong></span>
          <span class="chip">judgeable |Â| <strong>${judgeable.length}</strong></span>
          <span class="chip">correct |A∩R| <strong>${correct}</strong></span>
          <span class="chip">|R| <strong>${REF.size}</strong></span>
          <span class="chip">P <strong>${fmt(P)}</strong></span>
          <span class="chip">R <strong>${fmt(R)}</strong></span>
          <span class="chip">F1 <strong>${fmt(F1)}</strong></span>`;
      };
      renderAll();
    }
  }

  // ---------- Demo 2: ranking with NIL abstention ----------
  {
    const NIL = 'NIL (no equivalent)';
    const CANDS = ['stix:Identity', 'stix:IdentityContact', 'stix:Individual', 'stix:Infrastructure', 'stix:IntrusionSet', NIL];
    const list = document.getElementById('rd-list');
    const scoreBox = document.getElementById('rd-score');
    const nilToggle = document.getElementById('rd-nil-mode') as HTMLInputElement | null;
    if (list && scoreBox && nilToggle) {
      let order = [...CANDS];

      const gold = () => (nilToggle.checked ? NIL : 'stix:Identity');

      const render = (focusSpec?: { cand: string; dir: 'up' | 'down' }) => {
        list.innerHTML = '';
        order.forEach((c, i) => {
          const li = document.createElement('li');
          if (c === gold()) li.classList.add('gold');
          if (c === NIL) li.classList.add('nil-row');
          const iri = document.createElement('span');
          iri.className = 'iri';
          iri.innerHTML = c === NIL ? `<em>${c}</em>` : `<code>${c}</code>`;
          li.append(iri);
          if (c === gold()) {
            const tag = document.createElement('span');
            tag.className = 'badge badge-ok';
            tag.textContent = 'gold';
            li.append(tag);
          }
          const movers = document.createElement('span');
          movers.className = 'movers';
          const up = document.createElement('button');
          up.type = 'button';
          up.textContent = '↑';
          up.disabled = i === 0;
          up.setAttribute('aria-label', `Move ${c} up to rank ${i}`);
          up.addEventListener('click', () => {
            [order[i - 1], order[i]] = [order[i], order[i - 1]];
            render({ cand: c, dir: 'up' });
          });
          const down = document.createElement('button');
          down.type = 'button';
          down.textContent = '↓';
          down.disabled = i === order.length - 1;
          down.setAttribute('aria-label', `Move ${c} down to rank ${i + 2}`);
          down.addEventListener('click', () => {
            [order[i + 1], order[i]] = [order[i], order[i + 1]];
            render({ cand: c, dir: 'down' });
          });
          movers.append(up, down);
          li.append(movers);
          list.append(li);
        });

        // restore keyboard focus to the moved row's control after the re-render
        if (focusSpec) {
          const idx = order.indexOf(focusSpec.cand);
          const btns = list.children[idx]?.querySelectorAll<HTMLButtonElement>('button');
          if (btns?.length === 2) {
            const want = focusSpec.dir === 'up' ? btns[0] : btns[1];
            (want.disabled ? (focusSpec.dir === 'up' ? btns[1] : btns[0]) : want).focus();
          }
        }

        const rank = order.indexOf(gold()) + 1;
        const rr = 1 / rank;
        const h = (k: number) => (rank <= k ? 1 : 0);
        scoreBox.innerHTML = `
          <span class="chip">rank(gold) <strong>${rank}</strong></span>
          <span class="chip">RR <strong>${rr.toFixed(2)}</strong></span>
          <span class="chip">Hits@1 <strong>${h(1)}</strong></span>
          <span class="chip">Hits@3 <strong>${h(3)}</strong></span>
          <span class="chip">Hits@5 <strong>${h(5)}</strong></span>`;
      };
      nilToggle.addEventListener('change', render);
      render();
    }
  }
</script>
